  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Clothes to the Children of Afrin</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The ongoing military operation in Afrin have led to massive population displacement in Rural Aleppo and have impacted the protection and well-being of civilians who have remained inside Afrin. Children are among the most vulnerable groups who have been affected by the ongoing crisis.
This Project addresses the immediate need for seasonal clothes for the internally displaced children under 14 years settling in the collective shelters. Nearly 200,000 people have been displaced since the begining of Afrin crisis to Talll Refaat, Nabul and Zahara areas and surrounding villages. The number of the affected population is expected to increase. 
UNICEF has already responded to some of the need in different shelters with winter clothes. This project aims to provide the much needed summer clothes to the affected children by the on-going crisis.</narrative>
  </description>
